Erich Lutz



Test Scenarios for the Sign-up Flow and the Login Flow



I. Test Scenario - Verify the login of a Gmail account.
   A. Test Case - Enter a valid User Name and valid Password.
   B. Pre-Condition - A Valid Gmail account is needed to Login.
   C. Test Steps.
     1. Enter User Name
     2. Enter Password
     3. Click “Login” button
   D.	 Test Data
     1. <Valid User Name> 
     2. <Valid Password>
   E.	Expected Result - Successful login
   F.	Post Condition - User’s Email Inbox is shown.

II.	Test Case Two 
  A.	Test Case - Enter a valid User Name and an Invalid Password.
  B. 	Pre-Condition - A Valid Gmail account is needed to Login.
  C. 	Test Steps.
    1. Enter User Name
    2. Enter Password
    3. Click “Login” button 
  D. 	Test Data
    1. <Valid User Name> 
    2. <Invalid Password>
  E.	Expected Result - A message stating “The email and password you entered don’t   
      Match” is shown.
III.	Test Case Three
  A.	Test Case - Enter an Invalid User Name and a Valid Password.
  B. 	Pre-Condition - A Valid Gmail account is needed to Login.
  C. 	Test Steps.
    1. Enter User Name
    2. Enter Password
    3. Click “Login” button 
  D. 	Test Data
    1. <Invalid User Name> 
    2. <Valid Password>
  E.	Expected Result - A message stating “The email and password you entered don’t   
      Match” is shown.
IV.	Test Case Four
  A.	Test Case - Enter an Invalid User Name and an Invalid Password.
  B. 	Pre-Condition - A Valid Gmail account is needed to Login.
  C. 	Test Steps.
    1. Enter User Name
    2. Enter Password
    3. Click “Login” button 
  D. 	Test Data
    1. <Invalid User Name> 
    2. <Invalid Password>
  E.	Expected Result - A message stating “The email and password you entered don’t   
      Match” is shown.
